# RegWatch — Cursor Project Rules

## System Overview
RegWatch is a self-hosted web change detection system. changedetection.io
polls URLs, fires webhooks to a Flask app (port 5050), which triages diffs
via a local Ollama LLM and routes notifications by urgency.

## Six Development Rules (never violate these)
1. Config-Driven — all URLs, products, prompts are in YAML. No hardcoded values.
2. Detection, Not Correction — never modify product content. Output is always a notification.
3. Product Isolation — separate watches, logs, API scope per product.
4. Idempotent Triage — dedup by hash(url + diff + hour).
5. Ollama Sharing — share the instance, queue behind other jobs.
6. No Silent Failures — every error produces a log entry AND a fallback notification.

## Module Responsibilities (do not mix concerns)
- app.py → Flask app factory, webhook handler, health check
- config.py → YAML loading + lookup methods only
- triage.py → Ollama API calls + JSON response parsing only
- notify.py → Email + GitHub Issue creation only
- log.py → JSONL append + dedup + read queries only
- api.py → Flask blueprint for query endpoints only
- digest.py → Weekly digest compilation + sending only
- cli.py → CLI argument parsing + command dispatch only

## Code Style
- Python 3.11+ with type hints on all public functions
- Google-style docstrings on all modules, classes, public functions
- Specific exception types in try/except (no bare except)
- Use logging module, never print()
- Max ~200 lines per module

## YAML Config Schema (key reference)
- domains.yaml: products.{name}.{display_name, repo, notify, urgency_routing}
- watches/*.yaml: watches[].{url, check_interval, type?, css_selector?, keyword_filter?, context}
- watches[].context: {product, corridors?, likely_steps?, likely_fields?, categories?, note?}
- prompts/*_triage.yaml: {system, template} with {url}, {diff_text}, {corridors}, etc. placeholders

## Testing
- pytest with mocked HTTP (never call real Ollama/Resend/GitHub in tests)
- Test naming: test_{module}_{behaviour}_{scenario}
- Fixtures in conftest.py for sample configs and triage results
